28T06:20:28.641147+00:00","proposed_entity_type":"product_family","proposed_reasoning_summary":"Internal evidence clearly describes this as a tibial augment system for revision knee procedures with reversible/stackable design to address bone loss. 9 sizes with specified dimensions (AP: 36-51mm, ML: 27-37mm, 5mm thickness) confirm this is a product family of tibial augment blocks. Classification within 'Revision Knee Systems' division is appropriate. However, brand is empty and no material specification is provided - tibial augments are typically porous tantalum, trabecular metal, or solid metal alloy. Without external verification and missing critical metadata (brand identity beyond 'PCK' acronym, material composition), review is required to confirm material specification and verify PCK brand system details. No conflicts detected between available sources, but insufficient evidence exists to achieve high confidence without material data and brand clarification.","proposed_recommended_action":"send_to_review","proposed_semantic_anatomy_scope":["Proximal Tibia"],"proposed_semantic_brand_system":"PCK","proposed_semantic_coating_default":null,"proposed_semantic_confidence":0.85,"proposed_semantic_family_group":"PCK Revision Knee System","proposed_semantic_implant_class":"Tibial Augment Block","proposed_semantic_material_default":null,"proposed_semantic_parent_brand":"PCK","proposed_semantic_procedure_scope":["Revision Total Knee Arthroplasty","Bone Defect Reconstruction"],"proposed_semantic_review_required":true,"proposed_semantic_system_type":"Revision Knee Augmentation System","proposed_semantic_use_case_tags":["Bone Loss Management","Metaphyseal Defect","Stackable Augments","Reversible Design"],"proposed_web_verification_status":"review_required_ambiguity","semantic_anatomy_scope":["Proximal Tibia"],"semantic_brand_system":"PCK","semantic_coating_default":null,"semantic_confidence":0.85,"semantic_conflict_codes":[],"semantic_enriched_at":"2026-03-28T10:53:48.976648+0